<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;h3&gt;_Ch. 17 --  Daily weighing _&lt;/h3&gt;
It is what arrives of almost all the diseases that one flatters oneself to have cured. One has only passed them on, as one says in medicine, and one substitutes others for them.   -- SAINTE-BEUVE    &lt;u&gt;Mondays, I,&lt;/u&gt;  p. 19


